        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left"></span>
    </a>
    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#feature-carousel" data-slide="next">
        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right"></span>
    </a>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h3>A powerful BitTorrent client for Windows</h3>
        
        <p>
            Hadouken is a powerful, headless BitTorrent client for Windows. It runs as a Windows Service and you use the bundled web interface to manage it. Being headless, Hadouken is
            perfect for media servers where remote administration is the bee's knees.
        </p>

        <h4>Built on <em>libtorrent</em></h4>

        <p>Hadouken is built on <a href="http://www.libtorrent.org/">libtorrent</a> &mdash; a powerful and efficient C++ BitTorrent implementation used in various big-name clients.</p>

        <h4>Written in C#</h4>

        <p>By writing Hadouken in C#, we make it easy for contributors and developers to fix, enhance and create new features. Hundreds of unit tests make sure we do not accidentally break anything.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12">
        <h3>Remote administration</h3>

        <p>
            With the bundled web interface you can manage Hadouken from any computer or device with internet access. The interface is built with the Bootstrap framework, making it responsive and compatible with
            almost every browser.
        </p>
        
        <h4>HTTP/JSONRPC API</h4>
        
        <p>
            Hadouken comes with a HTTP/JSONRPC API allowing any application to integrate with Hadouken. Everything you can do via the web interface can also be done with JSONRPC &mdash; the web interface uses the exact same API.
        </p>
        
        <h4>PowerShell</h4>
        
        <p>The Hadouken PowerShell Cmdlets can be installed separate from Hadouken and gives you a powerful way of managing your Hadouken instance from a remote (or local) computer.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <h3>Push notifications</h3>
        
        <p>Hadouken supports a variety of 3rd party services for sending push notifications on various events, such as when a torrent is added or downloaded.</p>
        
        <h4>Supported services</h4>
        
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.pushbullet.com">Pushbullet</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://pushover.net/">Pushover</a></li>
            <li>SMTP integration</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <h3>Plugins</h3>
        
        <p>To increase versatility, Hadouken has an awesome plugin framework letting developers extend Hadouken with ease.</p>
        
        <p>For more information on how to write extensions, <a href="https://github.com/hadouken/hadouken/wiki">see the wiki</a>.</p>
    </div>
</div>